description: Officers were called to a home in Southport on Wednesday following a call from the ambulance service.
title: Police investigate unexplained death of woman
title_page: Southport: Police investigate unexplained death of woman - BBC News
maintext:
The death of a woman found at a home on Merseyside is being treated as unexplained, police have said.
Officers were called to Meols Cop Road in Southport just after 18:00 GMT on Wednesday after the ambulance service reported a woman had been found dead.
Merseyside Police said an investigation had been launched.
The force added: "Inquiries are ongoing to establish the full circumstances into the death."
